{
  "stem": "10588.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the whole tragedy comes [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I'm not going to go into the whole play.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But it was a play by, by Ansky's that I played.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And when I told it to my children, and they went to see it, they said, 'Mom, you were a little girl.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "How do you remember?' I said, 'Well, I guess God blessed me with a good memory.' Which is a blessing, and also a curse sometimes, because I remember what I had and what I lost.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So in a way, it's good.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Now, what type of religious background, upbringing did you have?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, my, my little brother started to go to Hebrew when he was only three years old, because that was required for boys in-- I started to go, I must have been about six years or so, started to go.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They had [NON-ENGLISH], they used to call it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Here, it would be called [NON-ENGLISH], you know, girl for school.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And to tell you the truth, I was a very good student in public school.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I liked when they talked about Yiddish history and everything.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But when they spoke in Hebrew, and I was kind always resisted to accept something that I couldn't understand, which I realize now was a mistake, because if I would have learned the words, later if I would get older I would learn the meaning.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But I had from the home, you know, because we observed the, all the Yiddish holidays and had the kashrut and had all the, you know, Jewish history and everything.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And so I've learned to see it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I spoke fluently Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I still do.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "At home with my husband, I only speak Yiddish, till this day and with most of my friends.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
